FYI I played around with this.  TPU instances are great but they won't work here for two reasons:
1. AWQ not (yet) supported according to https://github.com/vllm-project/vllm/issues/3620 so no 70b
2. logprobs not (yet) supported
The other thing is you don't get any speedup really until you jump up to a v5p-32 which is 4 nodes with 4 TPUs each, setup is a bit obnoxious, it takes forever to get quota from GCP if you even can, and it's only supported in us-east5-c for now which might be far away from your GPU instances.

That said...  It is faster, e.g. inference speeds on llama-3.1 8b instruct on some random prompts with 500 token output:
8x h100 sxm5: ~145 average tps
tpuv5p-32: ~185 average tps
So if you wanted to be a ninja and hack in support for AWQ and logprobs (then make it open source 😆 ) that would be swell
Also the tpuv5p-32 is $67/hr

# Nineteen 6.0

**Nineteen 6.0 is here - building on the all the work we've done already to extend even further!**

### TLDR
More competition from specialist miners, dynamic models for validators, easy access for any tao holder

## Making competition even more fierce
- Splitting of LLM & Image UIDS - lowering the barrier to entry.

## Any text or image model
- Any LLM (text-to-text) and any Image (text-to-image) model is supported - validators can take their pick and miners will continue to be rewarded for each model independently based on speed, capacity & consistency
- Extendable task configs so validators have their own priority independent of others - with mechanisms to keep vtrust high for all. 405B will come to 19!!

## Marketplace and API's - using Tao
- Marketplace on nineteen.ai/marketplace for users to see all the models each validator supports and all the providers
- Tao is bandwidth - use Tao to use 19! Validators can optionally provide bandwidth to their delegators based on their staked tao. Tao payments to follow!

## Misc
- Scoring period slightly reduced to 30 minutes for tighter feedback loops / greater miner flexibility when adjusting capacities
- Speed scoring based on quantiles and direct comparison with other miners

## Release
Set for Wednesday 1pm UTC. Validators will automatically update as usual, nothing to do there.
Miners will need to think about optimising their setups for different validator needs + separate UIDS

### Links for the next update
https://app.nineteen.ai/app/marketplace
https://app.nineteen.ai/app/api
